{
  "video_id": "KwIQy8xBOsk",
  "title": "The Market Revolution - part 1",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 569.0,
      "end_time": 2400.0,
      "text": "- [Instructor] So some\nhistorians have actually said"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2400.0,
      "end_time": 5579.0,
      "text": "that The Market Revolution\nis more revolutionary"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 5579.0,
      "end_time": 7448.0,
      "text": "than The American Revolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 7448.0,
      "end_time": 11969.0,
      "text": "Actually, this is a very\nclassic AP-US-history question."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 11969.0,
      "end_time": 13885.0,
      "text": "Which was more revolutionary:"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 13885.0,
      "end_time": 17665.0,
      "text": "The American Revolution\nor The Market Revolution?"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 17665.0,
      "end_time": 20349.0,
      "text": "But how could something\nactually be more revolutionary"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 20349.0,
      "end_time": 22748.0,
      "text": "than The American Revolution?"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 22748.0,
      "end_time": 24335.0,
      "text": "It's because The Market Revolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 24335.0,
      "end_time": 26918.0,
      "text": "was a confluence of inventions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 28482.0,
      "end_time": 32105.0,
      "text": "changes in the way that the\nAmerican people did business,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 32104.999999999996,
      "end_time": 35932.0,
      "text": "and changes in the way that\npeople got goods to market"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 35932.0,
      "end_time": 40324.0,
      "text": "that happened in this period\nfrom about 1790 to 1850."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 40324.0,
      "end_time": 43337.0,
      "text": "So this is kind of a\nlarge period of history,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 43337.0,
      "end_time": 45696.0,
      "text": "and I don't think it's\nreally important for you"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 45696.0,
      "end_time": 49412.0,
      "text": "to have a laundry list\nof dates of exactly when"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 49412.0,
      "end_time": 54310.0,
      "text": "what thing was invented, but\njust kind of take in the idea"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 54310.0,
      "end_time": 59280.0,
      "text": "that in the first half or\nso of the early 19th Century"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 59280.0,
      "end_time": 64239.0,
      "text": "there were many new inventions\nin both factory work"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 64239.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67043.0,
      "text": "and in transportation and communication,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 67043.0,
      "end_time": 71512.0,
      "text": "and that how people did\nbusiness changed a lot."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 71512.0,
      "end_time": 74318.0,
      "text": "So I wanna take some time to look into"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 74318.0,
      "end_time": 76901.0,
      "text": "all three of these revolutions:"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 77854.0,
      "end_time": 79995.0,
      "text": "The Industrial Revolution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 79995.0,
      "end_time": 83791.0,
      "text": "The Revolution in Transportation\nand Communication,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 83791.0,
      "end_time": 86159.0,
      "text": "and just the broader Market Revolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 86159.0,
      "end_time": 90067.0,
      "text": "So I know this is a subset of\nitself, but I'll get to that."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 90067.0,
      "end_time": 92508.0,
      "text": "And in this video I wanna\nstart out by talking"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 92508.0,
      "end_time": 95194.0,
      "text": "about The Industrial Revolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 95194.0,
      "end_time": 98083.0,
      "text": "OK, so what was The Industrial Revolution?"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 98083.0,
      "end_time": 100035.0,
      "text": "This was, broadly speaking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 100035.0,
      "end_time": 103202.0,
      "text": "a revolution in the kinds of machinery"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 105159.0,
      "end_time": 108492.0,
      "text": "that people used to make finished goods."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 110935.0,
      "end_time": 114435.0,
      "text": "Now, if you think about the early republic"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 115815.0,
      "end_time": 117686.0,
      "text": "in the United States you often think"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 117686.0,
      "end_time": 120269.0,
      "text": "of kind of an agrarian society;"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 121226.0,
      "end_time": 124684.0,
      "text": "and that was how Thomas Jefferson,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 124684.0,
      "end_time": 127247.0,
      "text": "the author of The\nDeclaration of Independence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 127247.0,
      "end_time": 129769.0,
      "text": "really imagined the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 129769.0,
      "end_time": 132781.0,
      "text": "as a nation of small farmers."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 132781.0,
      "end_time": 135585.0,
      "text": "But Thomas Jefferson\ndidn't necessarily see"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 135585.0,
      "end_time": 139865.0,
      "text": "all of these revolutions\nin industry coming."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 139865.0,
      "end_time": 141986.0,
      "text": "He couldn't anticipate that;"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 141986.0,
      "end_time": 144819.0,
      "text": "and so, in the 1790s, early 1800s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 146462.0,
      "end_time": 150533.0,
      "text": "a bunch of new inventions\ncame to the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 150533.0,
      "end_time": 154357.0,
      "text": "that completely revolutionized\nhow things were made."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 154357.0,
      "end_time": 156718.0,
      "text": "So in this time period the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 156718.0,
      "end_time": 159566.0,
      "text": "kinda slowly begins its transformation"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 159566.0,
      "end_time": 162066.0,
      "text": "from being a nation of farmers"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 163058.0,
      "end_time": 166641.0,
      "text": "to a nation of people\nwho worked for wages,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 168174.0,
      "end_time": 169679.0,
      "text": "by the hour,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 169679.0,
      "end_time": 172402.0,
      "text": "and then used the money that they made"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 172402.0,
      "end_time": 176569.0,
      "text": "from that hourly labor to buy\nthe things that they need."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 177568.0,
      "end_time": 179530.0,
      "text": "So how did this happen?"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 179530.0,
      "end_time": 183697.0,
      "text": "One event that historians often\npoint to is the introduction"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 185038.0,
      "end_time": 188948.0,
      "text": "of the textile mill to the United States."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 188948.0,
      "end_time": 193017.0,
      "text": "So this fellow here, his\nname is Samuel Slater,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 193017.0,
      "end_time": 196515.0,
      "text": "and Samuel Slater was an Englishman"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 196515.0,
      "end_time": 199023.0,
      "text": "who worked in a textile mill."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 199023.0,
      "end_time": 202789.0,
      "text": "And remember that the United Kingdom was"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 202789.0,
      "end_time": 207376.0,
      "text": "the world's capital of textile\nproduction in this time."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 207376.0,
      "end_time": 210511.0,
      "text": "And they were so jealous of their position"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 210511.0,
      "end_time": 213563.0,
      "text": "as the world's leading textile producer"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 213563.0,
      "end_time": 215963.0,
      "text": "that they even made it illegal"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 215963.0,
      "end_time": 219213.0,
      "text": "to export the plans for a textile mill."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 221167.0,
      "end_time": 224139.0,
      "text": "Samuel Slater decided that\neven if it was illegal"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 224139.0,
      "end_time": 226500.0,
      "text": "to export actual plans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 226500.0,
      "end_time": 230972.0,
      "text": "it wasn't necessarily\nillegal to export his brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 230972.0,
      "end_time": 233055.0,
      "text": "so he decided to memorize"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 236296.0,
      "end_time": 238879.0,
      "text": "how these textile looms worked;"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 240040.0,
      "end_time": 243123.0,
      "text": "and this is powered by a water wheel."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 244183.0,
      "end_time": 247266.0,
      "text": "And then he actually got in disguise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 248902.0,
      "end_time": 252766.0,
      "text": "put himself on a ship,\nand came to Rhode Island"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 252766.0,
      "end_time": 254849.0,
      "text": "to set up a textile mill."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 256879.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261107.00000000003,
      "text": "In fact, people were so\nangry that he did this that"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 261107.00000000003,
      "end_time": 264967.0,
      "text": "in his home town he's actually\nknown as Slater the Traitor."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 264967.0,
      "end_time": 266753.0,
      "text": "So what was new about this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 266753.0,
      "end_time": 270330.0,
      "text": "Well, I think the water-wheel aspect"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 270330.0,
      "end_time": 273173.0,
      "text": "is really one of the key innovations here."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 273173.0,
      "end_time": 276256.0,
      "text": "So instead of being powered by humans"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 277125.0,
      "end_time": 280180.0,
      "text": "or perhaps being powered by animals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 280180.0,
      "end_time": 284347.0,
      "text": "now American machinery can be\npowered by an outside source:"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 285917.0,
      "end_time": 290193.0,
      "text": "so water or steam; and\nthat means that these mills"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 290193.0,
      "end_time": 292797.0,
      "text": "and factories later are\ngoing to kinda congregate"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 292797.0,
      "end_time": 296534.0,
      "text": "around sources of power,\nlike rivers for example."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 296534.0,
      "end_time": 299545.0,
      "text": "So if you've ever wondered\nwhy so many American cities"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 299545.0,
      "end_time": 301297.0,
      "text": "are next to rivers, it's usually because"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 301297.0,
      "end_time": 304591.0,
      "text": "they needed them to power mills."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 304591.0,
      "end_time": 307436.0,
      "text": "So starting in the 1790s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 307436.0,
      "end_time": 310524.0,
      "text": "and really into the early 19th Century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 310524.0,
      "end_time": 314691.0,
      "text": "there's this slow transformation\ntoward factory labor."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 315608.0,
      "end_time": 318251.0,
      "text": "And you can see in this\nimage here that a lot"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 318251.0,
      "end_time": 321351.0,
      "text": "of the people actually\nlaboring in these factories"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 321351.0,
      "end_time": 325518.0,
      "text": "were women because young men\nkind of had a pretty good path"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 326608.0,
      "end_time": 329052.0,
      "text": "forward in life at this time period."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 329052.0,
      "end_time": 331815.0,
      "text": "They could be farmers, like their fathers;"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 331815.0,
      "end_time": 335025.0,
      "text": "maybe they could learn a trade."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 335025.0,
      "end_time": 337786.0,
      "text": "But for young women\nthere wasn't necessarily"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 337786.0,
      "end_time": 340304.0,
      "text": "a form of income outside the house,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 340304.0,
      "end_time": 343054.0,
      "text": "and so a man named Charles Lowell"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 344878.0,
      "end_time": 348011.0,
      "text": "decided to set up a whole series"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 348011.0,
      "end_time": 351836.0,
      "text": "of textile mills in what will be called"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 351836.0,
      "end_time": 353283.0,
      "text": "Lowell, Massachusetts."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 353283.0,
      "end_time": 355621.0,
      "text": "It's just outside of Boston."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 355621.0,
      "end_time": 359114.0,
      "text": "And then he primarily employed young women"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 359114.0,
      "end_time": 361191.0,
      "text": "to work in these textile mills."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 361191.0,
      "end_time": 363874.0,
      "text": "Think partly because young women"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 363874.0,
      "end_time": 367761.0,
      "text": "were associated with working with fabric;"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 367761.0,
      "end_time": 369649.0,
      "text": "women frequently did the spinning"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 369649.0,
      "end_time": 371002.0,
      "text": "and the sewing in the household;"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 371002.0,
      "end_time": 373810.0,
      "text": "but also because women\nyou could probably pay"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 373810.0,
      "end_time": 377977.0,
      "text": "a little bit less than young\nmen for the same kind of labor."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 381328.0,
      "end_time": 385067.0,
      "text": "So this is kind of a very slow revolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 385067.0,
      "end_time": 386984.0,
      "text": "toward individual work."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 390310.0,
      "end_time": 392893.0,
      "text": "Because as a nation of farmers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 394184.0,
      "end_time": 398291.0,
      "text": "most people would have\nworked in a family unit."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 398291.0,
      "end_time": 401221.0,
      "text": "And even some of the\nvery earliest factories"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 401221.0,
      "end_time": 404397.0,
      "text": "in the United States\nwould hire family units."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 404397.0,
      "end_time": 407511.0,
      "text": "It was known as the Rhode Island System."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 407511.0,
      "end_time": 410178.0,
      "text": "By this time, by Lowell's mills,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 411842.0,
      "end_time": 416009.0,
      "text": "he started hiring individual\nworkers for individual wages."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 416900.0,
      "end_time": 420997.0,
      "text": "And the working conditions\nwere pretty brutal."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 420997.0,
      "end_time": 424080.0,
      "text": "Most women at the Lowell mills worked"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 425169.0,
      "end_time": 429077.0,
      "text": "12-hour days with no air conditioning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 429077.0,
      "end_time": 431735.0,
      "text": "remember, this is long before\nthere's air conditioning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 431735.0,
      "end_time": 433230.0,
      "text": "for pretty low wages."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 433230.0,
      "end_time": 437134.0,
      "text": "I'd say probably about\nthree dollars a week."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 437134.0,
      "end_time": 440107.0,
      "text": "But despite the pretty harsh conditions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 440107.0,
      "end_time": 443399.0,
      "text": "for many of them this was\na really good opportunity"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 443399.0,
      "end_time": 445426.0,
      "text": "'cause this was the\nfirst time in their lives"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 445426.0,
      "end_time": 448967.0,
      "text": "they'd ever had any chance\nto make money of their own,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 448967.0,
      "end_time": 451040.0,
      "text": "to be away from their families."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 451040.0,
      "end_time": 455432.0,
      "text": "It's kind of expected that\nif you were a young woman"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 455432.0,
      "end_time": 459745.0,
      "text": "in Massachusetts you wanted to\ngo work in the Lowell mills."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 459745.0,
      "end_time": 463000.0,
      "text": "You could go there for a\nfew years of your life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 463000.0,
      "end_time": 464667.0,
      "text": "make a little bit of money,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 464667.0,
      "end_time": 468937.0,
      "text": "and then go back to your\nhometown, meet someone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 468937.0,
      "end_time": 471458.0,
      "text": "get married, start a family of your own."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 471458.0,
      "end_time": 473983.0,
      "text": "So if kinda makes work for women"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 473983.0,
      "end_time": 476400.0,
      "text": "outside the home respectable."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 477525.0,
      "end_time": 480136.0,
      "text": "And textile production\nis going to continue"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 480136.0,
      "end_time": 481923.0,
      "text": "to ramp up in the United States."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 481923.0,
      "end_time": 483340.0,
      "text": "In the late 1840s"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 485697.0,
      "end_time": 487530.0,
      "text": "a man named Elias Howe"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 488583.0,
      "end_time": 492246.0,
      "text": "invents a really excellent sewing machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 492246.0,
      "end_time": 495537.0,
      "text": "He's not the first man ever\nto invent a sewing machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 495537.0,
      "end_time": 497472.0,
      "text": "There were versions of\nthem stretching back"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 497472.0,
      "end_time": 500119.0,
      "text": "to think even the 1750s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 500119.0,
      "end_time": 502479.0,
      "text": "but Howe's sewing machine brought together"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 502479.0,
      "end_time": 505162.0,
      "text": "a lot of different capacities that made it"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 505162.0,
      "end_time": 506993.0,
      "text": "kinda the best sewing machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 506993.0,
      "end_time": 511489.0,
      "text": "And it will be even further\nrefined by Isaac Singer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 511489.0,
      "end_time": 514177.0,
      "text": "who we associate today with\nthe Singer Sewing Machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 514177.0,
      "end_time": 517010.0,
      "text": "And so these massive textile mills"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 518936.00000000006,
      "end_time": 523103.00000000006,
      "text": "really become the backbone\nof New England commerce."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 524592.0,
      "end_time": 526627.0,
      "text": "But, they never would have gotten started"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 526627.0,
      "end_time": 530794.0,
      "text": "without another invention,\nwhich was the cotton gin."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 532409.0,
      "end_time": 536576.0,
      "text": "And the cotton gin was invented\nby Eli Whitney in 1793."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 539169.0,
      "end_time": 541124.0,
      "text": "And what's important about the cotton gin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 541124.0,
      "end_time": 545432.0,
      "text": "so here's the gin, and\nbasically it's kind of a box"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 545432.0,
      "end_time": 549537.0,
      "text": "with some spikes on it\nthat allows you to take"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 549537.0,
      "end_time": 553704.0,
      "text": "these balls of cotton and\nseparate them from the seeds."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 554784.0,
      "end_time": 557466.0,
      "text": "And separating cotton from the seeds"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 557466.0,
      "end_time": 560883.0,
      "text": "was an extremely labor-intensive process."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 562436.0,
      "end_time": 565795.0,
      "text": "If you've never held a ball of cotton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 565795.0,
      "end_time": 569949.0,
      "text": "it's extremely sticky, so you\nkinda have to wade through"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 569949.0,
      "end_time": 574342.0,
      "text": "the little bits of cotton,\npull out these seeds."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 574342.0,
      "end_time": 575931.0,
      "text": "It takes forever."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 575931.0,
      "end_time": 579102.0,
      "text": "And so an average day's\nwork would not produce"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 579102.0,
      "end_time": 583007.0,
      "text": "all that much cotton that\nwas ready for market."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 583007.0,
      "end_time": 586269.0,
      "text": "Well, Whitney completely\nrevolutionizes this"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 586269.0,
      "end_time": 587618.0,
      "text": "with the cotton gin."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 587618.0,
      "end_time": 590057.0,
      "text": "These little spikes help separate"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 590057.0,
      "end_time": 592702.0,
      "text": "the cotton seeds from the cotton ball,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 592702.0,
      "end_time": 596364.0,
      "text": "and revolutionizes how\nmuch cotton can be produced"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 596364.0,
      "end_time": 598769.0,
      "text": "by a single person in a single day."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 598769.0,
      "end_time": 601943.0,
      "text": "Whitney's cotton gin made it\npossible for a single person"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 601943.0,
      "end_time": 606456.0,
      "text": "to process 50 pounds of\ncotton in a single day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 606456.0,
      "end_time": 609511.0,
      "text": "which is just an order of magnitude more"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 609511.0,
      "end_time": 612073.0,
      "text": "than they were able to do beforehand."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 612073.0,
      "end_time": 613703.0,
      "text": "This is really interesting 'cause it had"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 613703.0,
      "end_time": 617036.0,
      "text": "kind of a massive human cost in the form"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 618344.0,
      "end_time": 622208.0,
      "text": "of really bolstering the\ninstitution of slavery"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 622208.0,
      "end_time": 626237.0,
      "text": "in the American South\nbecause when farming cotton"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 626237.0,
      "end_time": 630062.0,
      "text": "was so labor-intensive it\nreally wasn't very profitable;"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 630062.0,
      "end_time": 632299.0,
      "text": "and so the institution\nof slavery was actually"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 632299.0,
      "end_time": 634863.0,
      "text": "starting to die out a little bit."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 634863.0,
      "end_time": 637857.0,
      "text": "Before the 1790s people were saying:"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 637857.0,
      "end_time": 642039.0,
      "text": "\"Eh, I don't know if it's\nactually worth it to keep slaves.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 642039.0,
      "end_time": 644194.0,
      "text": "So if it weren't for the cotton gin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 644194.0,
      "end_time": 646678.0,
      "text": "the United States might\nactually have outlawed slavery"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 646678.0,
      "end_time": 650845.0,
      "text": "considerably earlier than it\nended up doing in the 1860s."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 652339.0,
      "end_time": 656122.0,
      "text": "So it's interesting to\nnote that even though these"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 656122.0,
      "end_time": 659942.0,
      "text": "inventions really changed the\nfabric of American society,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 659942.0,
      "end_time": 661937.0,
      "text": "allowed some people to earn money"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 661937.0,
      "end_time": 664379.0,
      "text": "who had never been able\nto earn money before,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 664379.0,
      "end_time": 668045.0,
      "text": "it also meant that the\ninstitution of slavery"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 668045.0,
      "end_time": 670197.0,
      "text": "was really entrenched in the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 670197.0,
      "end_time": 674364.0,
      "text": "and would only continue\nto expand until the 1860s."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 675807.0,
      "end_time": 678288.0,
      "text": "So that's a little bit of a peak into"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 678288.0,
      "end_time": 681706.0,
      "text": "the human cost of The\nIndustrial Revolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 681706.0,
      "end_time": 685117.0,
      "text": "And we'll get more into what\nsome of those costs were"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 685117.0,
      "end_time": 689284.0,
      "text": "and what some of the benefits\nwere in the next video."
    }
  ]
}